  "notes": "Brasiliense / Candango (Brasรญlia, planned capital, 1960). Emerging koinรฉ from nationwide migration; converges on the southeastern (SP/MG) standard with Goiรกs/Central-West substratum. Encoded as the pt-BR base unchanged: /t,d/ palatalisation, dorsal onset /r/, tap coda /R/, alveolar coda /S/, coda /l/ -> [w], post-stressed reduction. Minimal dialect-specific divergence by design (levelling koinรฉ). Honestly a skeleton-tier delta by construction, not a research gap: Brasรญlia postdates Nascentes' (1953) six-subfalar division of Brazil by a decade (the city was inaugurated in 1960), so no historical subfalar exists to source a distinctive phonology from; the candango koinรฉ is a sociolinguistic contact outcome, not a settlement-era regional accent, and no read source documents a phonemic-level feature distinguishing it from the SP/MG-leaning standard it levelled toward.",
